Add Line Features (Classes) to Landscape

Source: R/add_lines.R
add_lines.Rd

description ...

Usage

add_lines(landscape, f, q, overlap)

Arguments

landscape

matrix a landscape matrix

f

vector (length based on number of desired line classes) frequency of given class, if q[i] = FALSE the frequency f[i] indicates the rate of patches connected by line features (ordered by area descending)

q

vector (length based on number of desired line classes) used for binning classification if q[i] = FALSE given class created by straight lines

overlap

vector landscape class to be overlapped with the given line class, if q[i] = FALSE patches of given class (overlap[i]) will be connected by the created line features

Value

landscape with added line features

Examples

add_lines(matrix(0, 100, 100), c(.005), c(.05), c(0))
